<dl id="n09072b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09072b">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09072b"> 72(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the <u>look</u> / 12 Pound look <small>Not cancelled</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n09072b"><li>FW 511.13 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/lexrA.htm#n09072b">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/l39rA.htm#n09072b">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n09072b">MS BL 47482b-106</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:226 <a name="rAd5" href="../../ff/fdra/rda.htm#rAd5">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/rA/rAd5.htm#n09072b">Draft: III&sect;3A.5</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;Quand un monstre survient au sein d&apos;une famille, dit Geoffroy-Saint-Hilaire, il &eacute;tonne, excite et trouble toutes les imaginations. &hellip; Cette infortun&eacute;e <font color="green">[= la m&egrave;re]</font>, sans songer que ses habitudes intellectuelles et ses connaissances tr&egrave;s born&eacute;es la rendent peu propre &agrave; aborder un aussi grave sujet de m&eacute;ditations, ne se donne au contraire pas de cesse qu&apos;elle n&apos;ait d&eacute;couvert ce qui l&apos;aura extraordinairement agit&eacute;e durant sa grossesse et ce qui aura caus&eacute;, par consequent, le d&eacute;veloppement d&eacute;sordonn&eacute; de l&apos;&ecirc;tre que ses flancs ont port&eacute;. &hellip; Ces opinions particuli&egrave;res, con&ccedil;ues et propag&eacute;es dans de semblables conjonctures, ont successivement servi &agrave; fonder la croyance populaire touchant l&apos;influence <mark><i>des regards</i> sur le d&eacute;veloppement d&apos;un embryon</mark>. <br><font color="green">[&ldquo;When a monster survives within a family&rdquo;, says Geoffroy- Saint-Hilaire, &ldquo;he surprises, excites, and troubles all the faculties of imagination.&hellip; This unfortunate person [the mother]</font>&mdash;without imagining that her intellectual habits and her very limited knowledge makes her unsuitable to tackle such a grave subject of thought&mdash;unfailingly does not doubt that what had extraordinarily agitated her during her pregnancy consequently caused the disturbed development of the being that her body had carried.&hellip; These particular opinions, conceived and propagated in similar unions, have successively served to establish the popular belief affecting the belief of the look upon an embryo&apos;s development.] <small> Caufeynon, <a name="CAUF" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CAUF"><cite title="source">Les Monstres Humains</cite></a> (Paris, 1900) 26</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: <cite>The Twelve Pound Look</cite> is a play by J. M. Barrie (1910). See JJII, 440.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c03104g" href="c3all.htm#c03104g">VI.C.03:104(g)</a>, <a name="c03104h" href="c3all.htm#c03104h">VI.C.03:104(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
